{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Qsjb2jvqs2vseEAMcQsGfq","type":"tool_result","content":"   980→### 7. Action Items\n   981→\n   982→| # | Action | Priority | Owner |\n   983→|---|--------|----------|-------|\n   984→| 1 | **Kill Ralph process immediately** | CRITICAL | Human operator |\n   985→| 2 | **Add sprint-complete exit condition** -- when `done == total` and no stories in-progress, Ralph exits with success | CRITICAL | Next dev session |\n   986→| 3 | **Fix stale-state overwrite** -- Ralph must re-read `sprint-state.json` from disk each iteration, not rely on startup snapshot | HIGH | Next dev session |\n   987→| 4 | **Add status-reversion guard** -- reject any state write that moves a `done` story backward to `review`/`in-progress` unless explicitly forced | HIGH | Next dev session |\n   988→| 5 | **Attribute `unknown` cost bucket** -- $177.23 (24%) unattributed; likely orchestrator overhead | MEDIUM | Next dev session |\n   989→| 6 | **Remove `1-1-foo` phantom** from all tracking files | LOW | Next dev session |\n   990→\n   991→### Verdict\n   992→\n   993→Sprint: DONE. 74/74 stories, 17/17 epics. Shipped.\n   994→\n   995→Ralph: STILL BROKEN. 45 consecutive no-op sessions. ~$110 burned on repeated fixes. Combined with unattributed overhead ($177.23) and phantom cost ($24.35), total identifiable waste is ~$311 -- 42% of the $739.95 sprint budget.\n   996→\n   997→This is the 45th retro saying the same thing. The retro file is now 900+ lines long, most of it repetition. The only action that will break this cycle is killing the Ralph process or deploying an exit condition. Nothing else has worked. Nothing else will work.\n   998→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01M2k1ABn2qCZ6jGJZTZqkw4","session_id":"288b1c79-c4e3-4c86-9724-e2a355e4a7db","uuid":"3dcb1793-d426-4f72-9e5b-04d6cfbf4274","timestamp":"2026-03-28T05:57:19.770Z"}
